li.p: VPMOVMSKB Compresses 32 bytes (0xFF/0x00) into a single 32-bit integer by extracting bit 7 of each byte.
TZCNT Counts trailing zeros. If byte 2 was the first 0xFF, bit 2 is '1', TZCNT returns 2.
Pointer Synthesis Adds the bit index to the chunk base address to get the absolute memory location.

div.p: Instruction: VPCMPEQB Micro-Op: dest[i] = (src1[i] == src2[i]) ? 0xFF : 0x00 Checks 32 bytes in a single clock cycle.
